<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am using the Oracle Instant Client connecting to a remote RAC database. The RAC system has multiple hosts. TNSnames.ora entry needs "LOADBALANCE clouth", "FAILOVER clouth", hostnames.
Therefore current PDO OCI module makes RAC TNSnames.ora entry too hard. 
Simply using "oci:dbname=mydb" (ZF1.0.3), I can connect RAC database.
I think PDO OCI module must contain both functions (1.0.3 + 1.7.0).
  * RAC = Real Application Cluster</p>

